Package org.ASUX.yaml

Class AbstractYamlEntryProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ASUX.yaml.AbstractYamlEntryProcessor
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DeleteYamlEntry, ListYamlEntry, ReadYamlEntry, ReplaceYamlEntry
    public abstract class AbstractYamlEntryProcessor
extends java.lang.Object

    This abstract class was written to re-use code to query/traverse a YAML file.

    This org.ASUX.yaml GitHub.com project and the org.ASUX.cmdline GitHub.com projects, would simply NOT be possible without the genius Java library "com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans".

    This abstract class has 4 concrete sub-classes (representing YAML-COMMANDS to read/query, list, delete and replace).

    See full details of how to use this, in Cmd as well as the org.ASUX.cmdline GitHub.com project.

    See Also:
    ReadYamlEntry, ListYamlEntry, DeleteYamlEntry, ReplaceYamlEntry

      • onPartialMatch

        protected abstract boolean onPartialMatch​(java.util.Map _map,
                                          YAMLPath _yamlPath,
                                          java.lang.Object _key,
                                          java.util.Map _parentMap,
                                          java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> _end2EndPaths)

        This function will be called when a partial match of a YAML path-expression happens.

        Example: if the YAML-Path-regexp is paths.*.*.responses.200.description

        This function will be called for: paths./pet paths./pet.put paths./pet.put.responses paths./pet.put.responses.200

        Note: This function will NOT be invoked for a full/end2end match for paths./pet.put.responses.200.description

        That full/end2end match will trigger the other function "onEnd2EndMatch()".

        Do NOT fuck with (a.k.a alter) the contents of any of the parameters passed. Use the parameters ONLY in Read-only manner. Got itchy fingers? Then, Deepclone both the parameters. YAMLPath class has a static member-function to make it easy to deepClone.

        Parameters:
        _map - This contains the java.utils.Map (created by com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans library) containing the YAML SUB-tree (Note: Sub-tree) of the YAML file, as pointed to by "_yamlPath" and "_key".
        _yamlPath - See the class YAMLPath @see org.ASUX.yaml.YAMLPath
        _key - The value (typically a String) is what matched the _yamlPath. Use it to get the "rhs" of the YAML element pointed to by _key
        _parentMap - A Placeholder to be used in the future. Right now it's = null
        _end2EndPaths - for _yamlPathStr, this java.util.LinkedList shows the "stack of matches". Example: ["paths", "/pet", "get", "responses", "200"]
        Returns:
        The concrete sub-class can return false, to STOP any further progress on this partial match

      • onEnd2EndMatch

        protected abstract boolean onEnd2EndMatch​(java.util.Map _map,
                                          YAMLPath _yamlPath,
                                          java.lang.Object _key,
                                          java.util.Map _parentMap,
                                          java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> _end2EndPaths)

        This function will be called when a full/end2end match of a YAML path-expression happens.

        Example: if the YAML-Path-regexp is paths.*.*.responses.200.description

        This function will be called ONLY for paths./pet.put.responses.200.description

        Partial matches (of "parent yaml-elements") will trigger the other function "onPartialMatch()".

        The words "onFullMatch" * "onCompleteMatch()" are confusing from user/regexp perspective. Hence the choice of onEnd2EndMath() as the function name.

        Do NOT fuck with (a.k.a alter) the contents of any of the parameters passed. Use the parameters ONLY in Read-only manner. Got itchy fingers? Then, Deepclone both the parameters. YAMLPath class has a static member-function to make it easy to deepClone.

        Parameters:
        _map - This contains the java.utils.Map (created by com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans library) containing the "bottom-most" YAML SUB-tree (Note: Sub-tree) of the YAML file, as pointed to by "_yamlPath" and "_key". This map could be potentially represent a simple YAML element like "name: petid"
        _yamlPath - See the class YAMLPath @see org.ASUX.yaml.YAMLPath
        _key - The value (typically a String) is what matched the _yamlPath. For "YAML Query", the "rhs" of the YAML element pointed to by _key is what you're looking for. For "YAML Delete" or "YAML Replace", you do Not care about the "rhs".. just use the _key to remove the entry/replace the "rhs".
        _parentMap - A Placeholder to be used in the future. Right now it's = null
        _end2EndPaths - for _yamlPathStr, this java.util.LinkedList shows the "stack of matches". Example: ["paths", "/pet", "get", "responses", "200"]
        Returns:
        The concrete sub-class can return false, to STOP any further progress on this partial match

      • onMatchFail

        protected abstract void onMatchFail​(java.util.Map _map,
                                    YAMLPath _yamlPath,
                                    java.lang.Object _key,
                                    java.util.Map _parentMap,
                                    java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> _end2EndPaths)

        This function will be called whenever the YAML path-expression fails to match.

        This will be called way too often. It's only interesting if you want a "negative" match scenario (as in show all rows that do Not match)

        Do NOT fuck with (a.k.a alter) the contents of any of the parameters passed. Use the parameters ONLY in Read-only manner. Got itchy fingers? Then, Deepclone both the parameters. YAMLPath class has a static member-function to make it easy to deepClone.

        Note: Unlike the other abstract methods of this Abstract class, this does NOT have a return-value.

        Parameters:
        _map - This contains the java.utils.Map (created by com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans library) containing the YAML SUB-tree (Note: Sub-tree) of the YAML file (as pointed to by "_yamlPath" and "_key") - representing where PathPattern match failed. This map could be potentially represent a simple YAML element like "name: petid"
        _yamlPath - See the class YAMLPath @see org.ASUX.yaml.YAMLPath
        _key - The value (typically a String) is what *FAILED* to match the _yamlPath.
        _parentMap - A Placeholder to be used in the future. Right now it's = null
        _end2EndPaths - for _yamlPathStr, this java.util.LinkedList shows the "stack of matches". Example: ["paths", "/pet", "get", "responses", "200"]

      • atEndOfInput

        protected abstract void atEndOfInput​(java.util.Map _map,
                                     YAMLPath _yamlPath)

        This function will be called when processing has ended.

        After this function returns, the AbstractYamlEntryProcessor class is done!

        You can fuck with the contents of any of the parameters passed, to your heart's content.

        Parameters:
        _map - This contains the java.utils.Map (created by com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans library) containing the entire Tree representing the YAML file.
        _yamlPath - See the class YAMLPath @see org.ASUX.yaml.YAMLPath

      • searchYamlForPattern

        public boolean searchYamlForPattern​(java.util.Map _map,
                                    java.lang.String _yamlPathStr)
                             throws com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans.YamlException

        Internal Note: This is NOT NOT NOT NOT NOT ........ a RECURSIVE-FUNCTION.

        This is a simple way to invoke the real-recursive function recursiveSearch(java.util.Map, org.ASUX.yaml.YAMLPath, java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String>).

        Parameters:
        _map - This contains the java.utils.Map (created by com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans library) containing the entire Tree representing the YAML file.
        _yamlPathStr - Example: "paths.*.*.responses.200" - ATTENTION: This is a human readable pattern, NOT a proper RegExp-pattern
        Returns:
        true = whether at least one match happened.
        Throws:
        com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans.YamlException - - this is thrown by the library com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans

      • recursiveSearch

        public boolean recursiveSearch​(java.util.Map _map,
                               YAMLPath _yamlPath,
                               java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> _end2EndPaths)
                        throws com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans.YamlException

        This is a RECURSIVE-FUNCTION. Make sure to pass in the right parameters.

        Don't tell me I did NOT warn you! Use the searchYamlForPattern(java.util.Map,java.lang.String) function instead.

        This function returns true, if the invocation (or it's recursion) did find a match (partial or end2end).
        For now, I'm Not using the return value ANYWHERE. Either I will - or - will refactor the return as Void.

        Parameters:
        _map - This contains the java.utils.Map (created by com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans library) containing the entire Tree representing the YAML file.
        _yamlPath - This is the YAMLPath class consstructed using example strings like "paths.*.*.responses.200" - ATTENTION: This string is a human readable pattern, NOT a proper RegExp-pattern
        _end2EndPaths - for _yamlPathStr, this java.util.LinkedList shows the "stack of matches". Example: ["paths", "/pet", "get", "responses", "200"]
        Returns:
        true = whether at least one match happened.
        Throws:
        com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans.YamlException - - this is thrown by the library com.esotericsoftware.yamlbeans
